'''Mitraba''' is a barren land in the northern [[Kuwait]] region. It currently holds the record of highest temperature ever recorded in [[Asia]] on 15 June 2010 when the [[mercury (element)|mercury]] rose up to 55&nbsp;°C (131&nbsp;°F).<ref>{{cite web|last=Fattahova|first=Nawara|title=Kuwait recorded highest temperature this year|url=http://www.kuwaittimes.net/read_news.php?newsid=MzEzNDg2ODYy|publisher=Kuwait Times|accessdate=27 July 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110617020438/http://www.kuwaittimes.net/read_news.php?newsid=MzEzNDg2ODYy|archivedate=17 June 2011|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kuwait's record highest temperature climbs to 54 degrees|url=http://www.china.org.cn/environment/2010-06/21/content_20311915.htm|accessdate=27 July 2010}}</ref>

