{{Use Australian English|date=January 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox book <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Reading Magic: How your child can learn to read before school - and other read-aloud miracles | image = | caption = | author = [[Mem Fox]] | illustrator = [[Judy Horacek]] | country = Australia | language = English | subject = [[Literacy|Reading literacy]], [[early childhood]] | published = 2001 ([[Macmillan Publishers|Pan Macmillan]]) | media_type = Print ([[paperback]]) | pages = 145 | isbn = 9780330362825 | oclc = 62537647 }}
'''''Reading Magic: How your child can learn to read before school - and other read-aloud miracles''''' is a 2001 book by [[Mem Fox]]. In it, Fox propounds reading books aloud to children from when they are babies to after they can read by themselves.
==Reception== In a review of ''Reading Magic'' ''[[BookList]]'' noted its "cheerful, chatty style that’s totally jargon-free" and recommended it for new parents.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Reading Magic: Why Reading Aloud to Our Children Will Change Their Lives Forever. |url=http://www.booklistonline.com/Reading-Magic-Why-Reading-Aloud-to-Our-Children-Will-Change-Their-Lives-Forever-Mem-Fox/pid=1099252 |journal=Booklist |publisher=American Library Association |accessdate=2 December 2016}}</ref> ''[[January Magazine]]''', in its review, wrote "Fox' book isn't some boring, didactic treatise on how to improve your child's reading skills. In fact, she's not at all fond of the phonics fanatics, and even discourages making your child read aloud to show their progress.",<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.januarymagazine.com/nonfiction/readinggames.html |title=Take Three Books and Call Me in the Morning |author=Pamela C. Patterson |date=May 2002 |website=januarymagazine.com |publisher=january magazine |accessdate=2 December 2016}}</ref> while ''[[Library Journal|Library Journal Review]]'' calls it a "rah-rah book on the benefits of reading aloud to children" and "A marginal purchase for public libraries."<ref name=gvpl/>
''Reading Magic'' has also been reviewed by ''[[Publishers Weekly]]''<ref name=gvpl/> and the ''[[School Library Journal]]''.<ref name=gvpl>{{cite web |url=https://m.gvpl.ca/s/Record/27659/Reviews |title=Reading magic : why reading aloud to our children will change their lives forever |website=m.gvpl.ca |accessdate=2 December 2016}}</ref>
